Arduino IDE Setup:

  File->Preferences->Additional Boards Manager URLs: 
  *  https://arduino.esp8266.com/stable/package_esp8266com_index.json
  *  Be sure to install v2.4.2 to avoid issue: https://github.com/esp8266/Arduino/issues/5787

  Install Libraries:
  *  AzureIoTHub
  *  AzureIoTUtility
  *  AzureIoTProtocol_MQTT
  *  ArduinoJson

-------------------------------------------------------------

Or build / upload directly from the command line:

  Install arduino-cli:
  *  curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/arduino/arduino-cli/master/install.sh | BINDIR=~/bin sh

  Configure arduino-cli:
  *  arduino-cli config init
  *  edit ~/.arduino15/arduino-cli.yaml and replace the board_manager line with:
     board_manager:
       additional_urls:
         - http://arduino.esp8266.com/stable/package_esp8266com_index.json
  *  arduino-cli core update-index

  Install dependencies:
  *  arduino-cli core install esp8266:esp8266@2.4.2
  *  arduino-cli lib install AzureIoTHub@1.0.45
  *  arduino-cli lib install AzureIoTUtility@1.0.45
  *  arduino-cli lib install AzureIoTProtocol_MQTT@1.0.45
  *  arduino-cli lib install ArduinoJson@6.10.0

  Build
  *  make 
     OR
  *  arduino-cli compile --fqbn esp8266:esp8266:huzzah

  Upload 
  *  make upload        # set serial port path in Makefile
     OR
  *  arduino-cli upload --fqbn esp8266:esp8266:huzzah -p /dev/[serial port name]
